☁️ Virtual Machine --------------------------
  In Google Cloud Platform, a VM is a compute instance provided by Compute Engine.

👉 Think of it as:
  A virtual server running in Google’s data centers
  You can install OS (Linux/Windows), apps, run workloads
  
  Key points:
    Runs on Compute Engine
    Fully customizable (CPU, RAM, disk)
    Pay-as-you-go

👉 Example:
  You launch a VM to run:
  Backend service
  Kubernetes node
  Jenkins server
